replies.body:
If you wanna reclassify a "?" mark as something not to be said then why use one in your post to explain it to me? It isn't my fault if you are annoyed by something that you misinterpret. If we redefine the "?" to be offensive I will stop using it, until then your being absurd.

{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-popcorn}}

If I see a questionable play not only is it my right to "?" (question) it, it's my duty as a productive member of the community to express my concern, which ironically is exactly the same action your doing by making this post. Just because I can do it more efficiently doesn't make me wrong, I have neither the time nor the patience to type all this out every game, for every play I see when such a handy tool designed by the game creators is at my disposal and is so much more efficient and effective (especially with the how did you word what you were thinking police scanning the logs every game and the bar for whats acceptable being adjusted to how it is).
